// Experiment 04 — Womersley Pulsatile Flow Through a Vessel Junction (No Graft)
//
// Inlet: codedFixedValue — Womersley pulsatile profile  (Aboelkassem & Virag 2019)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Same Womersley inlet as Experiment 04 (identical donor vessel R = 0.005 m = r1).
// The full Womersley solution replaces the parabolic approximation.
// At Womersley number α = R√(ω₀/ν) ≈ 7.45 the parabolic assumption is
// significantly inaccurate; the true profile is blunter at peak systole
// and shows near-wall flow reversal during the deceleration phase.
//
// Method (Womersley 1955; Aboelkassem & Virag 2019, Eq. 14):
//   1. The cardiac waveform U_mean(t) is Fourier-decomposed into N=8 harmonics.
//   2. For each harmonic n, a complex Womersley shape function W_n(η) is
//      precomputed (η = r/R ∈ [0,1]) using Bessel functions J₀, J₁.
//      Λ_n = R·√(i·n·ω₀/ν),  W_n(η) = [1 − J₀(Λ_nη)/J₀(Λ_n)] / [1 − 2J₁(Λ_n)/(Λ_nJ₀(Λ_n))]
//   3. Velocity at (r,t): U(r,t) = 2·U₀·(1−η²)           [DC Poiseuille]
//                                + Σₙ Re[Ûₙ · W_n(η) · e^(inω₀t)]  [harmonics]
//      where Ûₙ = Aₙ + i·Bₙ are the complex Fourier amplitudes.
//
// Shape functions stored as 60-point radial lookup tables (η=0 centre → η=1 wall).
// The Womersley shape functions satisfy W_n(1)=0 (no-slip at wall by construction).
//
// Cardiac waveform -- Holdsworth et al. (1999) archetypal CCA waveform:
//   PCHIP interpolation through physiological control points:
//     t_peak  = 0.142 s  (peak systole,   phi = 0.166T)
//     t_notch = 0.372 s  (dicrotic notch, phi = 0.434T)
//   Velocities: U_peak = 0.50 m/s, U_dia = 0.05 m/s
//   Dicrotic notch: U_notch = 0.10 m/s  (V_notch/V_peak ~ 0.20)
//   Q_peak ~ 39 mL/s,  Q_mean ~ 10.3 mL/s,  Q_notch ~ 7.9 mL/s
//   N=20 Fourier harmonics -- diastolic reconstruction error < 0.35 mL/s
//            Aboelkassem Y & Virag Z (2019) J. Theor. Biol. 462:499–513
//
// Outlet: inletOutlet — zero-gradient on outflow.
// Wall:   noSlip (covers upstream r1 cylinder, step face, downstream r2 cylinder).

